@kat_rhi_hai LLMs have so many parameters that you can fine-tune them to do virtually anything that can be done by a person on a computer (without leaving the desk or using the phone).

The problem is only in how to get the training data in enough quantities.

I think that in the future (or maybe they are already doing this), LLMs will be trained by asking a person to solve a task and recording everything they do on the screen, as well as asking the person to explain verbally in real time what they are doing and why.

